{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require ministers to be Members of the House of Commons and not the Lords",
        "additional_details": "The House of Lords is an unelected chamber. We believe the fact that government ministers, including Secretaries of State, can be appointed from this chamber, seems undemocratic given the decision-making power these individuals have.\r\n\r\nTherefore, we propose a ban on this so that our current, and future, governments are comprised entirely of elected ministers.",
        "background": "The UK government should pass a law banning the appointment of government ministers from the House of Lords, so that ministers can be appointed from the House of Commons only.",
